Akshay, from this documentary, clearly we can see the place where you'd stayed, has witnessed incredible progress toward equality for LGBTQ people, as well as the inevitable backlash following such a challenge to the status quo. The intensification of transphobic discrimination and violence is reflected in record numbers of cases such as lack of legal protections against discrimination, and proposed laws to bar trans people from using restrooms and other public facilities that correspond to their gender identity.  But this place as you've shown us has overcame with all such difficulties they've been facing and gives them a short span exaltation. It is very instrumental that we've to understand gender as social rather than biological phenomenon. But people fails to understand often and have created stereotypes against these community. Btw I came to know about this documentary from your whatsp status. I can't relate this but i must say It's very hard to do such things and for this, you really need a brave heart and positive impulses to ignore such backlashes from our surroundings. And that's what you're trying. Keep it up brother. I'm glad at least one of my friends is trying his best  to pursue his best interests. Lastly, My best wishes for your next adventures. ЁЯШЕЁЯЩМ

Sexual fluidity matlab na puri taraf se heterosexual aur na puri taraf se homosexual. Chance aur mahol ki baat hai aur kabhi kabhi koi physical appearance k karan attraction ho jata hai irrespective of gender.
5. Sexual fluidity ki tarah hi innate bisexuality ka bhi concept hai. Jaise jydatar janwaron(animals) aur pakshiyon (birds) me bhi dekha gaya hai ki vo bhi same sex karte hain. To mammals me by birth innate bisexuality hoti hai jiski wajah se hi vo same sex kar pate hain, yehi karan hai kisi kisi me ye attraction paida ho jata h.
6. LGBTQ population sirf bharat me hi 5% hai aur ye bhi vo hain jo khulke samne aye hain. Baki puri milayein to 10% k karib milenge, kyunki lgbt dating app pe bhi bahut log hain jo khud ko bahar heterosexual batate hain par fir bhi vo dating app use karte hain.

This video is full of misinformation. Gender and sex are two different things, there are lots of scientific research to prove that. Gender is something that has been assigned to you by your doctor and it can be very different from who you actually are, for ex. you can have a penis and still be a female. That's what transgender means, people who don't identify themselves as their assigned gender and that's why they change or go through hormonal changes. Also, research shows that more than 40% of men have more likely had sexual encounters with another man. So, it's not very rare and 100% natural. In India, we have 2.5 million people who identify themselves as LGBTQ and that's just people who aren't afraid of their identity. These types of videos are very homophobic and full of misinformation. If you really wanna know about LGBTQ community, go do your research on your own.
